<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1692,2005]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1437,151,285]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1692,1717]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">Description.</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity box="[454,540,1693,1717]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
(n= 
<number box="[587,600,1692,1717]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" value="5.0">5</number>
) in male, 
<quantity box="[712,797,1693,1717]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
(n= 
<number box="[847,857,1693,1717]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
) in female. Wing length: 
<quantity box="[1143,1229,1693,1717]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
(n= 
<number box="[1275,1289,1692,1717]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" value="6.0">6</number>
) in male, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="2.6">2.6 mm</quantity>
(n= 
<number box="[242,256,1729,1753]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" value="2.0">2</number>
) in female. 
<emphasis box="[394,454,1728,1753]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">Head</emphasis>
Frons bare in both sexes. Antenna 
<quantity box="[858,960,1729,1753]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="0.31">0.31 mm</quantity>
(n= 
<number box="[1009,1024,1729,1753]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" value="2.0">2</number>
). Antenna 
<number box="[1148,1183,1729,1753]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" value="0.8">0.8</number>
times in male and 
<number box="[1401,1436,1729,1753]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" value="1.2">1.2</number>
times in female as long as diameter of eyes. First flagellomere oval and enlarged near base, elongate as long tapering segment, sharpened like a straight long hair at tip; in male, flagellomere sometimes sharply curved at middle (
<figureCitation box="[244,326,1836,1861]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1119,1141]" captionTargetBox="[215,1375,373,1089]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[177,1390,341,1096]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 10. Litoleptis asterellaphile sp. n. (a) Antenna of male in lateral view [Rh 0204], (b) female genitalia in ventral view [Rh 0210], (c) male gonocoxite in dorsal (left) and ventral (right) view [Rh 0205]. Joint of gonocoxite and epandrium is circled and pointed by arrow. Scales = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271015/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number box="[296,326,1837,1861]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
a). 
<emphasis box="[359,417,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[432,512,1836,1861]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1119,1141]" captionTargetBox="[215,1375,373,1089]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[177,1390,341,1096]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 10. Litoleptis asterellaphile sp. n. (a) Antenna of male in lateral view [Rh 0204], (b) female genitalia in ventral view [Rh 0210], (c) male gonocoxite in dorsal (left) and ventral (right) view [Rh 0205]. Joint of gonocoxite and epandrium is circled and pointed by arrow. Scales = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271015/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number box="[484,512,1836,1861]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
b) Gonostylus slightly tapering toward apex (basal width at most 
<number box="[1242,1277,1837,1861]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" value="1.8">1.8</number>
times as wide as width of narrowest part), posterior surface of apex hollowed and posterior margin projected as truncated, upward apex inwardly. Sperm sac bulbous not visible in ventral view. Lateral ejaculatory process baculiform. Ejaculatory apodeme moderately long but not reaching anterior margin of gonocoxite. Posteromedial margin in ventral surface of gonocoxite bear one bristle. Aedeagus smoothly connected with paramere at wide joint. 
<emphasis box="[1226,1310,1980,2005]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1330,1414,1980,2005]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1119,1141]" captionTargetBox="[215,1375,373,1089]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[177,1390,341,1096]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 10. Litoleptis asterellaphile sp. n. (a) Antenna of male in lateral view [Rh 0204], (b) female genitalia in ventral view [Rh 0210], (c) male gonocoxite in dorsal (left) and ventral (right) view [Rh 0205]. Joint of gonocoxite and epandrium is circled and pointed by arrow. Scales = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271015/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number box="[1386,1414,1981,2005]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
c) Spermatheca membranous, long and narrow, less than half as wide as long. Spermathecal duct accessory gland with short, sclerotized columnar duct curves middle at right angle, arising at approximately three-fourth distal length from genital chamber to spermathecal ducts. Common spermathecal duct absent. Genital chamber oval, very narrow, occupying fraction of sternite 
<number box="[580,594,260,284]" pageId="12" pageNumber="53" value="9.0">9</number>
area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
