<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="53" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1242,1760]" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1386,1411]" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a noun in apposition, formed by the combination of ” 
<taxonomicName box="[1178,1278,1386,1411]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aytoniaceae" genus="Asterella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="12" pageNumber="54" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">asterella</taxonomicName>
”, which being named after the genus of their host-plant, and “phile”, a suffix that derived from Latin and means “lover of”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="53" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1242,1760]" box="[199,896,1458,1483]" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">
