</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1242,1760]" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,390,1493,1518]" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">Natural history.</emphasis>
Habitat of this species is rocky cliff along streams and roads in deciduous forests. Larvae of this species are thallus miners of 
<taxonomicName box="[520,694,1530,1555]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aytoniaceae" genus="Asterella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="12" pageNumber="53" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="odora">
<emphasis box="[520,694,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">Asterella odora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[708,873,1530,1555]" class="Marchantiopsida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Marchantiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="53" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="order">Marchantiales</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[883,1026,1530,1555]" class="Marchantiopsida" family="Aytoniaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Marchantiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="53" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="family">Aytoniaceae</taxonomicName>
). Adults emerged in spring (April, in laboratory condition).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="53" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1242,1760]" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1602,1627]" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[328,595,1602,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" genus="Litoleptis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asterellaphile">
<emphasis box="[328,595,1602,1627]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">Litoleptis asterellaphile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is smaller in body size than the other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1140,1246,1602,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" genus="Litoleptis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1140,1246,1602,1627]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">Litoleptis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known in 
<collectingCountry box="[1365,1432,1603,1626]" name="Japan" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">Japan</collectingCountry>
. This species can be distinguished from the other 
<taxonomicName box="[696,802,1635,1660]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" genus="Litoleptis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[696,802,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">Litoleptis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in 
<collectingCountry box="[925,989,1636,1659]" name="Japan" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">Japan</collectingCountry>
by the following characters: gonostylus slightly tapering toward apex (basal width at most 
<number box="[724,759,1669,1693]" pageId="12" pageNumber="53" value="1.8">1.8</number>
times as wide as width of narrowest part), posterior surface of apex hollowed and posterior margin projected as truncated, upward apex inwardly; posteromedial margin in ventral surface of the gonocoxite bear one bristle; lateral ejaculatory process baculiform.
</paragraph>
